column106:
The first days in Mannheim there were lots of changing energetic states. From utter sleep deprivation when I had to get up at 6.30 the first monring, to make sure my son gets to his first school day on time, after having had the drive from Brussels to Mannheim while I stopped in Aachen to meet my 40 year old girlfriends from elementary school. Our conversations brought us obviously closer to the "endlichkeit der eigenen Existenz" and to see how familiar it all was and the sense of this being the life as it should be (archetype). These moments of transition really get me so out of my body, that it is difficult to bear, every minute change in energetic or electromagnetic disposition of my system is being registered by my consciousness. 
After 2 good nights of sleep and a good swim that settled down. Max has arrived at destination at his farm workshop and I can start working on all my work related loose ends.
